HEADWORD: Prefrontal
<hw>Pre*fron"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat. &
Zool.)</fld> <def>Situated in front of the frontal bone, or the frontal
region of the skull; ectethmoid, as a certain bone in the nasal capsule
of many animals, and certain scales of reptiles and fishes.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A prefrontal bone or scale.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prefulgency</ent>⟦br⟧
